    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1942-03-29T08:35:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1942-03-29T08:35:00-05:00" n="381"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d381">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">891.00/1851: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Minister in Iran</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Dreyfus</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Tehran</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1942-03-29T17:00:00+03:25"
                            >March 29, 1942—5 p.m.</date>
                        <lb/> [Received 8:37 p.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>85. Reference to my 61 of March 11, 5 p.m., the Prime Minister informs me the
                    Cabinet at last night’s meeting formally agreed to expel the Japanese Legation.
                    Japanese Minister will be informed of this action within next few days.</p>
                <p>Referring to Department’s 66, March 13, 6 p.m.<note n="86" xml:id="d381fn86">
                        <hi rend="italic">Ante</hi>, <ref target="#pg_289">p. 289</ref>.</note> and
                    my 84,<note n="87" xml:id="d381fn87">Dated March 29, not printed.</note> Prime
                    Minister feels it would strengthen his hand in explaining this action to Majlis
                    if he could announce some concrete indications of American economic assistance
                    particularly if he could make public the extension of Lend-Lease aid to
                        Iran.<note n="88" xml:id="d381fn88">For correspondence on this subject, see
                            <ref target="#pg_289">pp. 289</ref> ff.</note>
                </p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Dreyfus</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
